{"name":"alm_asset","description":"Manages the lifecycle of assets from procurement to retirement.","summary":"In ServiceNow, the object `{alm_asset}` typically refers to the Asset Management (ALM) module, which is designed to manage and track the lifecycle of assets within an organization. Hereâ€™s a summary of its key components and functionalities:\n\n1. **Asset Tracking**: Keeps a comprehensive record of all assets, including hardware, software, and virtual assets. It tracks details such as ownership, location, and status.\n\n2. **Lifecycle Management**: Manages the entire lifecycle of assets from procurement through to retirement. This includes stages like acquisition, deployment, maintenance, and disposal.\n\n3. **Inventory Management**: Helps maintain an accurate inventory of all assets, ensuring that asset data is up-to-date and accessible.\n\n4. **Financial Management**: Tracks financial information related to assets such as depreciation, cost, and budget allocation.\n\n5. **Compliance and Auditing**: Ensures that assets comply with regulatory and organizational policies. Facilitates audits by maintaining detailed records and histories of assets.\n\n6. **Reporting and Analytics**: Provides tools for generating reports and analytics to gain insights into asset utilization, performance, and trends.\n\n7. **Integration**: Integrates with other ServiceNow modules like Incident Management, Problem Management, Change Management, and Configuration Management Database (CMDB) to provide a holistic view of IT operations.\n\nThe `{alm_asset}` object plays a crucial role in optimizing asset utilization, reducing costs, and ensuring compliance within an organization.","attributes":[{"name":"parent","type":"reference"},{"name":"skip_sync","type":"boolean"},{"name":"product_instance_id","type":"string"},{"name":"residual_date","type":"glide_date"},{"name":"residual","type":"currency"},{"name":"sys_updated_on","type":"glide_date_time"},{"name":"request_line","type":"refere